[[cdo:3 nguŏk 26 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 26 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:三月廿六]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 26''' is the 26th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1259]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Shōka|ja|正嘉}} to {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元}}. * {{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳}} 1st year / {{ill|Genchū|ja|元中}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1390]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kōō|ja|康応}} to {{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳}}. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1829]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日}}) – In connection with the Siebold incident, a new death sentence was pronounced against {{ill|Takahashi Kageyasu|ja|高橋景保}}, who had been imprisoned. * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate received the steam warship “{{ill|Kaiyōmaru|ja|開陽丸}}” on order from the Netherlands.
== Births == {{Expand section}}
== Deaths == * {{ill|Entoku|ja|延徳|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1489]] {{ill|April 26|ja|4月26日}}) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshinobu|ja|足利義尚}}, the 9th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1465]])<ref>{{Kotobank|足利義尚}}</ref>. * {{ill|Shōhō|ja|正保|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1646]] {{ill|May 11|ja|5月11日}}) – {{ill|Yagyū Munenori|ja|柳生宗矩}}, a Kenjutsu master and father of {{ill|Yagyū Sanjūrō|ja|柳生三厳（十兵衛）}} (born [[1571]]).
