{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 26''' is the 26th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1259]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Shōka|ja|正嘉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year / {{ill|Genchū|ja|元中|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1390]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kōō|ja|康応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1829]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In connection with the Siebold incident, a new death sentence was pronounced against {{ill|Takahashi Kageyasu|ja|高橋景保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, who had been imprisoned. * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate received the steam warship “{{ill|Kaiyōmaru|ja|開陽丸|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}” on order from the Netherlands.
