{{Not to be confused with|March 26|qq=March 26}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 26일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 26''' is the 26th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōgen|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1259|1259]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Shōka (era)|Shōka]] to {{ill|Shōgen|ja|正元|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōgen|qq=}}. * [[:en:Meitoku|Meitoku]] 1st year / [[:en:Genchū|Genchū]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1390|1390]] [[:en:April 12|April 12]]) – The Northern Court changed its era name from [[:en:Kōō|Kōō]] to [[:en:Meitoku|Meitoku]]. * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1829|1829]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – In connection with the Siebold incident, a new death sentence was pronounced against {{ill|Takahashi Kageyasu|ja|高橋景保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takahashi Kageyasu|qq=}}, who had been imprisoned. * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1867|1867]] [[:en:April 30|April 30]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate received the steam warship “[[:en:Japanese frigate Kaiyō Maru|Kaiyōmaru]]” on order from the Netherlands.
== Births == {{Expand section|qq=}}
== Deaths == * [[:en:Entoku|Entoku]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1489|1489]] [[:en:April 26|April 26]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshihisa|Ashikaga Yoshinobu]], the 9th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1465|1465]])<ref>{{Kotobank|足利義尚|qq=}}</ref>. * [[:en:Shōhō|Shōhō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1646|1646]] [[:en:May 11|May 11]]) – [[:en:Yagyū Munenori|Yagyū Munenori]], a Kenjutsu master and father of {{ill|Yagyū Sanjūrō|ja|柳生三厳（十兵衛）|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yagyū Sanjūrō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (born [[:en:1571|1571]]).
